200.description:
The OpenAPI 3.1 document for this fylr instance, as JSON.
The body is a full OpenAPI spec — too large to model inline;
consume it with an OpenAPI parser.

parameters.description:
Datamodel version. `HEAD` returns the working copy;
`CURRENT` resolves to the most recently committed version;
numeric ids return a specific committed snapshot.

Reindex behaviour for changes that need it. `skip` = none;
`reindex` = background; `reindex_block` = background plus a
temporary frontend lock. Omit to be prompted via a `202`.

version.description:
Produced-version reference in the form `<class>.<version-name>`
(e.g. `video.preview`). Only relevant when `type` = `version`;
the `<class>` part must equal the file's class.

id.description:
Numeric id of the stored plugin. Assigned by **fylr** on create;
must be absent (or `0`) in a `PUT` create body, and must match the
path `{id}` in a `POST` update body.

parameters.description:
Machine-readable details. `ObjectInsufficientRights` carries
`objecttype`, `systemobjectid`, `right` and `rightdisplayname`;
`SystemRightRequired` carries `rights`.

Machine-readable, code-specific details.
`RightRequired` carries `right` and `rightdisplayname`;
`CollectionObjectInsufficientRights` carries `systemobjectid`,
`displayname`, `owner`, `right` and `rightdisplayname`;
`SystemRightRequired` carries `rights`.

uuid.description:
Transport UUID. Auto-assigned for pure download transports;
may also be supplied on input and is used to log in to the
export.

info.description:
Type-specific parameters. Shapes for built-in types:
`set_tags` -> `{"tags":[{"_id":<tag id>,"set":true|false}]}`;
`change_owner` -> `{"owner":<WhoApi>}`;
`email` -> `{"subject":<LocaValue>,"message":<LocaValue>,"batchable":<bool>,"recipients":[<WhoApi>]}`;
`webhook` -> `{"name":<configured webhook name>,"callback":"pre_save"|"after_commit_async"}`
(callback defaults to `after_commit_async`).
Plugin action types carry whatever the plugin declares.

UserCollectionPinCodeApi.description:
A pin code the user holds for a pin-protected collection. Set by
the user when they unlock the collection for the first time;
re-verified on each subsequent access.

statuscode.description:
HTTP status, repeated here. `409` for `ExportDuplicateName`;
`404` for `FileNotFound`; `400` for the remaining
download / validation codes.
